408→                           Conjectured by Bollobás and Erdős. Bollobás and Shelah have confirmed this for $k=1$. Proved by Gyárfás <a href="#cite-Gy92-58" onclick="event.preventDefault();addNewBox('Gy92','58'); return false;">[Gy92]</a>, who proved the stronger result that, if $G$ is 2-connected, then $G$ is either $K_{2k+2}$ or contains a vertex of degree at most $2k$. <br><br>A stronger form was established by Gao, Huo, and Ma <a href="#cite-GaHuMa21-58" onclick="event.preventDefault();addNewBox('GaHuMa21','58'); return false;">[GaHuMa21]</a>, who proved that if a graph $G$ has chromatic number $\chi(G)\geq 2k+3$ then $G$ contains cycles of $k+1$ consecutive odd lengths.
